This paper is about weakly-supervised neural text classification, which falls under the natural language processing (NLP) domain. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a method that involves pre-training and model refinement, which suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Additionally, the paper deals with text classification, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the proposed method involves deep neural models, which is a common topic in the deep learning (cs.DL) category.
